  "articleSummary": "The article argues that each generation overestimates the threat of new technologies (e.g., calculators, CliffsNotes, GPS) while underestimating society’s capacity to adapt. It frames AI as the latest \"technological bogeyman,\" emphasizing that historical fears of intellectual decay have repeatedly proven unfounded. The author advocates for **teaching AI literacy**—helping students discern when AI enhances or undermines learning—and **revising educational practices** to align with AI-augmented realities. The tone is analytical yet hopeful, using historical parallels to counter panic. Intended for educators and policymakers, the piece stresses proactive adaptation over resistance, framing AI as a tool to be mastered, not a dystopian inevitability.",
